<subSubSection lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[113,1089,1330,1577]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,1330,1353]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SPAETH F." box="[229,392,1330,1353]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="183 - 187" refId="ref51295" refString="SPAETH F. 1931 b: Wissenschaftliche Ergebnise der Swedischen Entomologischen Reisen des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas und Bahia 1914 - 15 und 1923 - 24. Cassidinae. Entomologisk Tidskrift 53: 183 - 187." type="journal article" year="1931">SPAETH (1931b)</bibRefCitation>
compared this species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Spaeth, 1905" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1905" box="[659,1088,1330,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateripunctata">
<emphasis box="[659,946,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Cistudinella lateripunctata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SPAETH F." box="[951,1088,1330,1353]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="79 - 118" refId="ref50803" refString="SPAETH F. 1905: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen V. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 55: 79 - 118." type="journal article" year="1905">Spaeth, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boheman, 1854)" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[158,449,1362,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiata">
<emphasis box="[158,256,1362,1385]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">C. apiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BOHEMAN C. H." box="[270,441,1362,1385]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" refId="ref47930" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1854: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Secundus. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 506 pp. + 2 pls." type="book" year="1854">Boheman, 1854</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
because of the yellowish-brown body with coarse punctures on the explanate margin of elytra, but stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1931" box="[642,761,1394,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiana">
<emphasis box="[642,761,1394,1417]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">C. bahiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from both in the shape of pronotum and punctation of elytra. 
<bibRefCitation author="HINCKS W. D." box="[515,667,1426,1449]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="545 - 559" refId="ref49747" refString="HINCKS W. D. 1956: Some Neotropical Cassidinae (Col., Chrysomelidae) in the Museum G. Frey. Entomologischen Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey 7: 545 - 559." type="journal article" year="1956">HINCKS (1956)</bibRefCitation>
followed Spaeth and placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1931" box="[971,1088,1426,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiana">
<emphasis box="[971,1088,1426,1449]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">C. bahiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in couplet with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1905" box="[280,462,1458,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateripunctata">
<emphasis box="[280,462,1458,1481]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">C. lateripunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his key to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[719,849,1458,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[719,849,1458,1481]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Cistudinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[113,1089,1330,1577]" lastBlockId="38.[151,1127,220,435]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">
All species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[295,425,1490,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,425,1490,1513]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Cistudinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by the posterior angles of pronotum forming an acute angle, which is more or less projecting backwards, particularly in males while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">C. bahiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the basal corners of pronotum broadly rounded therefore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1931" box="[870,990,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiana">
<emphasis box="[870,990,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">C. bahiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[256,386,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[256,386,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="313">Cistudinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In my opinion 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1931" box="[553,670,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cistudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiana">
<emphasis box="[553,670,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="313">C. bahiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[791,871,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[791,871,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="313">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it exhibits the typical diagnostic traits of this genus: long antennae with four basal shiny and sparsely pubescent antennomeres, flat body, bare apex of elytra and simple tarsal claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1127,220,435]" pageId="38" pageNumber="313">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Spaeth" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[181,353,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiana">
<emphasis box="[181,353,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="313">Orexita bahiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the group of species with regularly convex elytra and explanate margin of elytra with sparsely arranged coarse punctures, see thesis 5a in 
<bibRefCitation author="SPAETH F." box="[936,1086,348,371]" pageId="38" pageNumber="313" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
but differs from all in small size of body and so far it is the smallest species of the genus.
</paragraph>
